# libFuzzer / cargo-fuzz artifacts.
#
# `target/` is the build output for the fuzz workspace; `corpus/`
# accumulates interesting inputs the fuzzer has discovered;
# `artifacts/` holds crashes / hangs / OOMs reproducers.
#
# The corpus seed files we *want* in git live under `corpus_seeds/`
# (NOT git-ignored). When a fuzz run finds something interesting,
# the maintainer copies the relevant `corpus/<target>/<hash>`
# entry into `corpus_seeds/<target>/` and `tests/parser_corpus.rs`
# loads it back as a regression test.

target/
corpus/
artifacts/
